              }
            }
          ],
          "mechanicsEvidence": {
            "status": "draft",
            "notes": [
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The damage increase is usually additive with other damage mods like Point Blank , with exceptions where it is multiplicative. See Condition Overload (Mechanic) for more details."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The damage increase is not applied on the hit that procs a new status effect, it is only applied on following hits ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For example: Galvanized Aptitude has 2 stacks, weapon has 100 base damage and Primed Point Blank for a total of 100 * (1 + 1.65 ) = 265 damage. First hit procs Impact and deals 265 damage. Then on the following hit the +80% damage from the 2 stacks is applied for a total of 100 * (1 + 1.65 + 0.8 ) = 345 damage."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "However, Multishot instances are treated as sequential hits, allowing a weapon with multishot to benefit from the damage increase even on the first trigger pull. For example: Galvanized Aptitude has 2 stacks, weapon has 100 base damage, Primed Point Blank , and a multishot of 3. The first multishot instance deals 100 * (1 + 1.65 ) = 265 damage and procs Impact . The second multishot instance will then apply the +80% damage from 2 stacks, for a total of 100 * (1 + 1.65 + 0.8 ) = 345 damage. If the second instance procs Puncture , then the third instance will apply +160% damage (80% for two stacks times 2 different status effects), for a total of 100 * (1 + 1.65 + 1.6 ) = 425 damage. Thus, in one trigger pull the weapon will have dealt 1035 total damage, instead of the 795 that would have been dealt otherwise."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "When the buff times out, one stack is lost and the buff duration resets."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Only kills from a weapon equipped with this mod will give stacks, and only the weapon equipped with this mod will benefit from the buff. If equipped on both a normal weapon and an Exalted Weapon , it will affect both weapons."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Kills from status procs (including from Hunter Munitions ) from a weapon equipped with this mod will give stacks."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Bonus damage from status procs may originate from any source, including primary and secondary weapons, Warframe abilities, companions, other players, or the environment."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Impact , Puncture , Slash , Cold , Electricity , Heat , Toxin , Blast , Corrosive , Gas , Magnetic , Radiation , Viral , and Void procs all count for the damage bonus."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Lifted from Melee Heavy Attacks also counts."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Nukor and Kuva Nukor apply a unique invisible status called Microwave to enemies touched by its beam."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Microwave procs have infinite duration."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Although knockdown does not cause any icon on the enemy, it still counts as a status."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Note that conditions or abilities that prevent knockdowns (e.g. Bastille ) will prevent it from increasing damage."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Galvanized Savvy",
                  "pageId": 1549354,
                  "revisionId": 2654939,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Since Lifted and knockdown will cancel out each other, the maximum number of status effects that can be applied to an enemy is 16."
                }
              }
            ],
